Manufacturer of home products, Aspira Nigeria Limited, has signed prolific Nigerian music artiste, Davido, as the brand ambassador for its Viva plus brand. The company announced this at a conference in Lagos on Thursday. Speaking at the event, Head, Marketing and Advertising, Aspira Nigeria, Santhosh Nair, said the synergy between both brands would impact the society in positive and significant ways. According to him, the brand had formed the partnership because of the alignment of Davido’s vision and the core values of Viva as a brand. He said, “We are glad to announce that henceforth Davido will be the official face of our Viva brand. “We decided to sign because of his dynamism, popularity among Nigerian youths and his hard working disposition which has put Nigeria on the global music map. He’s no doubt through his music making Nigerians proud. “He has contributed immensely towards the entertainment industry in Nigeria. He continues to inspire millions of Nigerian youths and this is in consonance with the core values at Aspira.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com